## Naming conventions
- Functions: snake_case
- Classes: PascalCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Files: snake_case (Python) / kebab-case (TypeScript/JavaScript)

## Code structure
- Keep functions small (< 40 lines as a guide)
- One responsibility per function
- Prefer explicit over implicit

## Comments
- Comment WHY, not WHAT
- No commented-out code in commits
- TODO comments must include a ticket/issue reference

## Error handling
- Handle errors at the boundary — don't swallow silently
- Log errors with context (not just `except: pass`)

## Testing
- New features require tests
- Bug fixes require a regression test
- Test files mirror the source file structure

## Git commits
- Use conventional commits: feat/fix/docs/refactor/test/chore
- Commit message subject: imperative mood, ≤ 72 characters
- Decisions in commit body: use "decided", "chose", "switched" keywords

## Dependencies
- No new dependencies without team discussion
- Prefer stdlib/built-in over third-party where practical
